HEADWORD: Lurg
<hw>Lurg</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
large marine annelid (<spn>Nephthys c⟦ae⟧ca</spn>), inhabiting the sandy
shores of Europe and America. It is whitish, with a pearly luster, and
grows to the length of eight or ten inches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lurid</ent>⟦br⟧
